Fantastic--chocolaty, nutty--and very easy. Rave reviews. I blind baked the crust as others suggested. I also made 50% more filling like many suggested and it was way too much for a store bought 9 inch regular [NOT DEEP DISH] pie crust. The specified quantities would have been perfect. Also, the cooking time is perfect for this shallow 9" pie and the center was not gooey or liquidy at all. Maybe the others used a deeper dish pie form. Now, I did omit the bourbon. I also substituted hazlenuts for pecans b/c I love the chocolate-hazlenet combination. It was fabulous and doesn't need the liquor if you don't want it.

