Rating: 4
I'm partial to homemade crusts, so I used my own recipie (1c. flour, 1/8tsp salt, 1/3 c. shortening, 4 tbsp water) for that, which worked v. well. Loved this pie so much I made it twice in 2 days (hooray for Derby time!). 1st time I made it exactly as directed, but sub'd walnuts for pecans (personal preference), which worked great. Second time I made it I futzed: I used 3 tbsp bourbon instead of 1; added 1/2 c. more walnuts to make up for the more liquidy nature of filling (due to additional bourbon); added 1 tsp chipotle pepper for a kick (i love chipotle pepper w/anything chocolate). Turned out fabulous! This recipie is v. easy to adjust to one's tastes, and still turns out great. For best results, be sure to use good quality chocolate (I used Callebaut brand 60% bittersweet). I'll be making it again no doubt.

